      • outputOpeningFormTag

        void outputOpeningFormTag()

      • outputOpeningFormTag

        void outputOpeningFormTag(@Nullable
                          String name,
                          @Nullable
                          FormMethod method,
                          @Nullable
                          Boolean hasFileInput,
                          @Nullable
                          String className)
        Output the opening portion of a form tag, such as, <form action="someurl" method="post">.
        Parameters:
        name - optional name of the form. This name should be unique for the document.
        method - optional method. Default is "get".
        hasFileInput - optional boolean that determines the content type of the data that is posted to the server. If the form will have an input element of type file, pass in true. Default is false.
        className - optional CSS class name. Class names should have already had HTMLUtil.normalizeClass(CharSequence) called on them if the source is unknown.

      • outputOpeningFormTag

        void outputOpeningFormTag(@Nullable
                          String name,
                          @Nullable
                          FormMethod method,
                          @Nullable
                          Boolean hasFileInput,
                          @Nullable
                          String className,
                          PrintWriter writer)
        Output the opening portion of a form tag, such as, <form action="someurl" method="post">.
        Parameters:
        name - optional name of the form. This name should be unique for the document.
        method - optional method. Default is "get" if the form does not contain a file input.
        hasFileInput - optional boolean that determines the content type of the data that is posted to the server. If the form will have an input element of type file, pass in true. Default is false.
        className - optional CSS class name. Class names should have already had HTMLUtil.normalizeClass(CharSequence) called on them if the source is unknown.
        writer - the writer. Use if you need to override the writer.
